              ወፈነዎ ፡ ኀበ ፡ ታኦፊላ ፡ ዘጸሐፈ ፡ ሎቱ ፡ ቀዳሚ ፡ ወንግለ ።</title>
              <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
              <rubric>Chapters irregularly marked and not numbered.</rubric>
              <explicit xml:lang="gez">እስከዝ ፡ ነገር ፡ አብጽሐ ፡ ሉቃስ ፡ በዜናሁ ። ወእምዝ ፡ ተስወረ ፡ እምኔሁ ፡
              እስመ ፡ አንተ ፡ ትረክበ ፡ በቀዳሚ ፡ ፍካሬ ፡ መልእክተ ፡ ጳውሎስ ፡ ዜና ፡ ግብረ ፡ ጳውሎስ ። እስመ ፡ ውእቱ ፡ ቦአ ፡
              ኀበ ፡ ኔሮን ፡ በቀዳማይ ፡ ጊዜ ፡ ሞአ ፡ ወሖረ ፡ በሰላም ። ወእምድኅረዝ ፡ ነበረ ፡ ኑኀ ፡ ፪ዓመታተ ፡ 
              ወወጽአ ። ወእምዝ ፡ ተመይጠ ፡ ወአጥመቀ ፡ አዝማዲሁ ፡
              ለኔሮን ፡ ወስምዓ ፡ ኮነ ፡ በአዴሁ ፡ በሰይፍ ፡ ዕጉሠ ።</explicit>
              <explicit xml:lang="en">Luke brought his account until here. You will find what is missing here
                at the beginning of the exposition of Paul's epistle, that is  the <title ref="LIT1016Actsof">Acts of Paul</title>. He went to <persName ref="PRS7550Nero">Nero</persName>, 
              triumphed and went away in peace. Then he stayed for two years and left. Then he
              returned and baptised <persName ref="PRS7550Nero">Nero</persName>'s parents and patiently became a martyr by his hands, by the
              sword.</explicit>
              <note>The text generally agrees with that of <bibl><ptr target="bm:Platt1830novum"/></bibl>,  which represents the revised version.</note>
